: 250.782ms
```

### Motivation

I very often need to group elements of a list and immediately apply some transformation to the grouped sub-lists or their elements. It‚Äôs usually quite ineffective to do it in two steps (requires another loop with nested loop and intermediate arrays).

I‚Äôm quite sure that it‚Äôs very common need so there _must be_ some ‚Äústandard‚Äù name for such function. I‚Äôve tried to find something in Haskell, but without success. Eventually I found a function named `reduceBy` which does what I need in these two libs:
- [itertoolz.reduceby](http://toolz.readthedocs.org/en/latest/api.html#toolz.itertoolz.reduceby) (Python), 
- [CloudFlow.reduceBy](https://github.com/mbraceproject/MBrace.Core/blob/7de07474e7ed32adc90a66c93c6e8fa279577a14/src/MBrace.Flow/Combinators.fs#L646-L666) (F#).
#### Example 1

``` js
const students = [
  { name: 'Lucy', score: 92 },
  { name: 'Drew', score: 85 },
  // ...
  { name: 'Bart' score: 62 },
]
const grade = (n) => (n < 65) ? 'F' : (n < 70) ? 'D' : (n < 80) ? 'C' : (n < 90) ? 'B' : 'A'
const byGrade = R.pipe(R.prop('score'), grade)

// A. Using R.groupBy and nested pair of R.map:
const namesByGrade = R.pipe(
  R.groupBy(byGrade),
  R.map(R.map(R.prop('name')))
)

// B. Using new R.reduceBy:
const namesByGrade = R.reduceBy(byGrade, (acc, stud) => acc.concat(stud.name), [])

namesByGrade(students)
// {
//   'A': ['Lucy'],
//   'B': ['Drew'],
//   // ...
//   'F': ['Bart'],
// }
```
#### Example 2

``` js
const tweets = [
  { author: '@drboolean', text: 'Lorem ipsum', favs: 60 },
  { author: '@dan_abramov', text: 'dolor sit amet', favs: 80 },
  { author: '@drboolean', tex: 'consectetur', favs: 40 },
  // ...
]

// A. Using R.groupBy, R.map and nested R.reduce:
const sumFavsByUser = R.pipe(
  R.groupBy(R.prop('author')),
  R.map(R.reduce((acc, tw) => acc + tw.favs))
)

// B. Using new R.reduceBy:
const sumFavsByUser = R.reduceBy(R.prop('author'), (acc, tw) => acc + tw.favs, 0)

sumFavsByUser(tweets)
// {
//    '@drboolean': 100,
//    '@dan_abramov': 80,
// }
```
### Transducer?

I‚Äôve implemented also `_xreduceBy` transducer, but I‚Äôm not sure how to use it (and so how to test it). How can be `groupBy` used with `R.transduce` or `R.into`?

